            <div>
                <opener><dateline>March 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1775</dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I fear I sent my last away without subscribing but if you knew the weight on me
                    in producing a full &amp; true account of y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> country
                    you wd not blame. nor w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>
                    <persName ref="pe0157">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Macgovan</persName> refuse me a
                    drawing of <rs ref="ar0065">his image</rs>. Thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    Letters &amp; acc<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi> of the hospitals. if <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0141">Ballendine</title></bibl> is very imperfect I
                    had rather wait till another casts up being a little finical about my books.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am <lb/>Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obliged
                        humble Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed></closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> other pacquets ab<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                        nationâ€™s hospitals are just come.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
